  "prompt": "Who is the old man in the MDH Masala ads and why does he appear in all their ads?",
  "response": "The old man in the MDH Masala ads is Dharampal Gulati, who was the founder and managing director of MDH (Mahashian Di Hatti) Masala, a well-known spice brand in India. He became a recognizable face of the brand due to his consistent appearances in advertisements, where he would promote the various spice products offered by MDH.\n\nDharampal Gulati's presence in the ads helped humanize the brand and build a strong emotional connection with consumers. His persona conveyed trustworthiness and tradition, which resonated with many customers. The ads typically showcased him sharing recipes and the benefits of using MDH spices, further establishing the brand's credibility in the spice market.\n\nHis popularity and the nostalgic appeal of his character made the ads memorable, leading to MDH becoming one of the leading spice brands in India. Dharampal Gulati remained a prominent figure in the advertising campaigns until his passing in November 2020. After his death, the brand announced it would continue to honor his legacy while adapting to modern advertising strategies.",
